summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $65.00 out of the general fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of Walter W. Powers for damages done to house owned by claimant located at 1322 Alki Avenue, Seattle, said damages being occasioned by the breaking of a sewer pipe located on 45th Avenue Southwest, adjacent to said premises, which flooded said premises with mud and debris, on or about the 10th day of February, 1916, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
